modules.description: Copies data between memory regions using direct byte manipulation, supports alignment-aware transfers and size-based optimization. Operates on raw byte arrays and unboxed data structures for low-level memory management. Used to efficiently transfer large datasets in network protocols and binary file parsing.

Provides functions to copy data between OCaml bytes, bigarrays, C pointers, and arrays with optional offset and length parameters. Supports safe and unsafe memory access specifications, ensuring bounds checking or bypassing it as needed. Enables direct memory transfers from strings and bytes to various memory structures.
